    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look poised for a high-ceiling outing, anchored by a trio of offensive threats against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** leads the charge with a standout 74.56 score, bolstered significantly by a favorable matchup against the high-xERA L\u00f3pez and a prime #2 lineup spot. Joining him in capitalizing on this matchup is **Brady House** (63.81), whose strong platoon advantage and batting order stability make him a core contributor for today. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** serves as our premier utility option; his 74.92 score is a direct result of his elite xwOBA and a soft landing against Jack Kochanowicz, effectively bypassing any concern regarding his minor platoon splits.\n\nWhile **Kyle Tucker** (77.10) remains our most statistically potent start, the 35% rain risk in his contest warrants close monitoring, as any weather-shortened game would cap his upside. Tactical flexibility remains key, as seen in the benching of **Marcell Ozuna** (53.80). **Marcell Ozuna** was the closest to cracking the active roster, but the optimizer ultimately prioritized the superior matchup-based efficiencies of **Nasim Nunez**\u2014whose speed-first profile and 62.09 score reflect our team-wide mandate to maximize stolen base potential against shaky opposing arms. \n\nFinally, managers should note that while **Gunnar Henderson** (57.76) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (51.43) are active, their scores are dampened by elite \"hold\" pitchers who historically suppress stolen base opportunities. We are accepting the marginal floor in exchange for the high-end power potential they provide in the top third of our lineup. With **Liam Hicks**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Josh Lowe**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages** all maintaining their roles, the squad is well-positioned to navigate the volatility of a busy Monday. We remain vigilant on **Jordan Westburg**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Josh Jung**, 